name: io.bytes.per.checksum
description:
The number of bytes per checksum.  Must not be larger than
  io.file.buffer.size.

name: ipc.[port_number].decay-scheduler.period-ms
description:
How frequently the decay factor should be applied to the
    operation counts of users. Higher values have less overhead, but respond
    less quickly to changes in client behavior.
    This property applies to DecayRpcScheduler.

name: dfs.client.read.striped.threadpool.size
description:
The maximum number of threads used for parallel reading
    in striped layout.

name: mapreduce.job.speculative.minimum-allowed-tasks
description:
The minimum allowed tasks that
  can be speculatively re-executed at any time.

name: ipc.client.idlethreshold
description:
Defines the threshold number of connections after which
               connections will be inspected for idleness.

name: ipc.maximum.data.length
description:
This indicates the maximum IPC message length (bytes) that can be
    accepted by the server. Messages larger than this value are rejected by the
    immediately to avoid possible OOMs. This setting should rarely need to be
    changed.

name: dfs.client.read.short.circuit.replica.stale.threshold.ms
description: Threshold in milliseconds for read entries during short-circuit local reads.

name: hadoop.security.kms.client.encrypted.key.cache.expiry
description:
Cache expiry time for a Key, after which the cache Queue for this
    key will be dropped. Default = 12hrs

name: fs.s3a.fast.upload.active.blocks
description:
Maximum Number of blocks a single output stream can have
    active (uploading, or queued to the central FileSystem
    instance's pool of queued operations.

    This stops a single stream overloading the shared thread pool.
